{
  "texts": [
    "In Study 2, we investigated the treatment's influence on participants' behavioral intentions (see SM section 5).",
    "We found that the treatment significantly increased intentions to ignore or unfollow social media accounts espousing the focal conspiracy (𝛃 =.39 [.27,.50], p <.001; Figure 4C and Table S19) and significantly increased willingness to ignore or argue against people who believe the focal conspiracy (𝛃 =.42 [.31,.54], p <.001; Figure 4D and Table S20).",
    "There was a directional but non-significant decrease in intentions to join pro-conspiracy protests (𝛃 = -.12 [-.27,.03], p =.12; Figure 4E and Table S21) -intentions which were low at baseline, potentially creating a floor effect.",
    "Although it was not possible for us to ensure that all the claims produced by the AI in our experiment were accurate, we hired a professional fact-checker to evaluate the veracity and potential bias of all 128 claims made by GPT-4-turbo across representative example conversations from each of the 11 major conspiracy clusters generated by participants in our experiments.",
    "Of these claims, 127 (99.2%) were rated as \"true\", 1 (0.8%) as \"misleading\" and 0 as \"false\"; and none of the claims were found to contain liberal or conservative bias."
  ]
}